narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned about Bayesian Inference and its applications to biological research problems.

In this course, I focused on learning topics and developing skills that are essential to the data work-flow. The major topics involved include the following: data engineering, relational databases, SQL, data acquisition, data visualization, machine learning, and the foundations with shelland condaand Git. Throughout this course, I was able to gain more familiarity with the applied methods and techniques that are used in industry, improve my skills in using these tools to think about and solve real-world problems, and practice communicating and presenting technical knowledge.
